At the time of writing this, the method org.eclipse.wst.server.core.internal.Module.equals(...) is as follows:

	public boolean equals(Object obj) {
		if (!(obj instanceof IModule))
			return false;

		IModule m = (IModule) obj;
		if (!getId().equals(m.getId()))
			return false;
		//if (!project.equals(m.getProject()))
		//	return false;
		//if (!getModuleType().equals(m.getModuleType()))
		//	return false;

		return true;
	}

This bug is to restore the commented out project check when testing module equality (and you should also add a null check for project).

Without this change the WTP functionality fails in several places if two modules in the workspace target the same name on deployment.

Affiliation: IBM
Release: 1.5
Justification: Two projects with the same deployed name is a fringe use-case for WTP but for the IBM Rational Developer product there are components for which this is the normal case so this behaviour functioning correctly is critical.

